{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βᾰρύς</b>, εῖα, ύ, <br /> <i>poetry</i> <i>genitive</i> <i>plural</i> <i>feminine</i> βαρεῶν uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 932 (_anapaest meter_): _comparative_ βαρύτερος, _superlative_ βαρύτατος\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:— <b>heavy in weight,</b> β. ἀείρεσθαι, opposed to κοῦφος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.150, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 152d, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Caelo” 310b25, etc.: in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] mostly with collateral notion of <b>strength and force,</b> χεῖρα βαρεῖαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.219, compare 89; ἀκμᾷ βαρύς 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).51; β. τὸ σῶμα 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Μακεδονική” 14 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of athletes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “de gymnastica” 31 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ὀφρύς <b>bushy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 48 \">Refs</a>]; but also, <b>heavy with age, infirmity</b> or <b>suffering,</b> νόσῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 235; σὺν γήρᾳ [prev. author] “OT” 17; ἐν γήρᾳ [prev. author] “Aj.” 1017; ὑπὸ γήρως 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 9.1; ὑπὸ τῆς μέθης 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.596a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>pregnant,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PGoodsp.Cair. 15.15 (4th c.AD)\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]; β. βάσις <b>heavy, slow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 966; τυπάδι βαρείᾳ [prev. author] “fragment” 844 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> κοῦφον βαρέως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 189d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>heavy to bear, grievous,</b> ἄτη, ἔρις, κακότης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.111, 20.55, 10.72; Κλῶθες 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.197; κῆρες 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.548; β. κὴρ τὸ μὴ πιθέσθαι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 206 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; βαρὺ or βαρέα στενάχειν sob <b>heavily,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.95, 534, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.334, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: in Trag. and Prose, <b>burdensome, grievous, oppressive,</b> β. ξυμφορά, τύχαι, καταλλαγαί, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 1044 (Lyric poetry), “Th.” 332 (Lyric poetry), 767 (Lyric poetry), etc.; ἡδονή 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1204; ἀγγελία β. ἢν ἐν τοῖς βαρύτατ᾽ ἂν ἐνέγκαιμι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 43c; πόλεμος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.241; βαρὺ κοὐχὶ δίκαιον [prev. author] 21.66; νόσος \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>causing disgust,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1330; αὐδά, ἠχώ, [prev. work] 208 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 791 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>unwholesome,</b> χωρίον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.6.12; πλησμονή [prev. author] “Cyn.” 7.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>indigestible,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 3.115e; β. νότος 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 10.17.11. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <i>adverb</i> -έως, φέρειν τι take a thing <b>ill,</b> suffer it <b>impatiently,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.19; β. φέρειν ἐπί τινι 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 15.1.1 (but β. φέρειν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] bear <b>with dignity,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 26.3)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; β. ἔχειν, with part, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica ad Alexandrum” 1424b5; πρός τι [prev. author] “Pol.” 1311b9 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τοῖς λογίοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Arg. Euripides Tragicus “Heracl.” \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> βαρυτέρως τινὶ ἐναντιωθῆναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.3Mac.3.1 \">LXX</a>]; βαρέως ἀκούειν hear <b>with disgust,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.1.9. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>violent,</b> ὀργή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 368; μῆνις [prev. author] “OC” 1328; ἀπέχθειαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 23a (_superlative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θυμός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 1.96. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>weighty, grave,</b> ἐπιστολαί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.2Cor.10.10; αἰτιώματα NT.Act.25.7; τὰ βαρύτερα τοῦ νόμου NT.Matt.23.23 \">NT</a>]; <b>ample,</b> βαρυτάτην εὐδαιμονίαν τοῖς ἀρχομένοις παρέξειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 2.14.3. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of persons, <b>severe, stern,</b> β. ἐπιτιμητής [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 77; εὔθυνος [prev. author] “Pers.” 828, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 546; Κύπρι βαρεῖα 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 1.100 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>wearisome, troublesome,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 894, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 210c, etc.; ξύνοικος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 415, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 753; γείτονες 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.10.6. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>overbearing,</b> σεμνότεροι ἢ βαρύτεροι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1391a27 (but σεμνὸς καὶ β. 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 14.1.42); ὑπερήφανοι καὶ β. 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.279c \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>important, powerful,</b> πόλις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.17.5, etc. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of soldiers, <b>heavy-armed,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.3.37 (assuming variant) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the ὁπλίτης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 833b (_comparative_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ β. τῶν ὅπλων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.76.3. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>difficult,</b> ὅρκος γὰρ οὐδεὶς ἀνδρὶ φηλήτῃ β. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 933. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> of impressions on the senses, <br /><Level3><b>__III.1</b></Level3> of sound, <b>strong, deep, bass,</b> opposed to to ὀξύς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.257, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 208, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 332c, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1125a14, etc.; βαρὺ ἀμβόασον 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 572 (Lyric poetry); φθέγγονται βαρύτατον ἀνθρώπων 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 15; βαρύτατα ὑπακούειν, of diseases, [prev. author] “Prorrh.” 2.39; πενθεῖν 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 12.1 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; especially of musical pitch, <b>low,</b> opposed to ὀξύς, βαρυτάτη χορδή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 268e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἆχος, φωνά, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Archytas Tarentinus Philosophus I, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Eudemia” 1235a28, 4th c.BC: Aristoxenus Musicus “Harmonica” p.3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] M.; of accent, <b>grave,</b> ἀντὶ ὀξείας τῆς μέσης συλλαβῆς βαρεῖαν ἐφθεγξάμεθα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 399b; ὀξείᾳ καὶ βαρείᾳ καὶ μέσῃ φωνῇ 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1403b30, etc.: hence ἡ βαρεῖα (i.e. προσῳδία)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>accentus gravis,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Dionysius Thrax Grammaticus 630.1, etc.; β. τάσις 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 11, 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 307.13; β. τόνος 2nd c.BC: Dionysius Thrax Grammaticus 674.13, compare 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 36.5; β. συλλαβή \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<b>unaccented,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Synt.” 100.8, +others\">Refs</a>] <i>adverb</i> βαρέως <b>with the accent thrown back,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pron.” 51.1, 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 2.53b: _comparative_ -ύτερον, opposed to ὀξύτερον \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] (ου) opposed to οὗ), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Sophistici Elenchi” 178a3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (but, <b>on a lower note,</b> αὐλεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “GA” 788a22). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> of smell, <b>strong, offensive,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.119. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <i>adverb</i> βαρέως <b>slowly,</b> ἐπισπᾶσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus “Automatopoetica” 26.6 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]. (<b>guṛr-u-</b> from <b>gu[rmacr]ṛ-u-,</b> Sanskrit <i>gurús</i> 'heavy', Latin <i>gravis</i> (from <i>feminine</i> <b>gur[schwa]wī-</b>), Gothic <i>kaúrus</i> 'heavy'.)","strongNumber":"G0926","accentedUnicode":"βαρύς","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0004","matchingForm":"ἀβαρής","stepTransliteration":"abarēs","gloss":"not burdensome","_zh_tw_Gloss":"無重擔","_es_Gloss":"sin carga","_zh_Gloss":"无重担"},{"strongNumber":"G0916","matchingForm":"βαρέω","stepTransliteration":"bareō","gloss":"to burden","_zh_tw_Gloss":"困倦","_es_Gloss":"cargar","_zh_Gloss":"困倦"},{"strongNumber":"G0917","matchingForm":"βαρέως","stepTransliteration":"bareōs","gloss":"difficultly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"發沉","_es_Gloss":"dificultad","_zh_Gloss":"发沉"},{"strongNumber":"G0922","matchingForm":"βάρος","stepTransliteration":"baros","gloss":"burden","_zh_tw_Gloss":"重擔","_es_Gloss":"carga","_zh_Gloss":"重担"},{"strongNumber":"G0927","matchingForm":"βαρύτιμος","stepTransliteration":"barutimos","gloss":"expensive","_zh_tw_Gloss":"極貴","_es_Gloss":"caro","_zh_Gloss":"极贵"},{"strongNumber":"G1912","matchingForm":"ἐπιβαρέω","stepTransliteration":"epibareō","gloss":"to burden","_zh_tw_Gloss":"受累","_es_Gloss":"cargar ","_zh_Gloss":"受累"},{"strongNumber":"G2599","matchingForm":"καταβαρέω","stepTransliteration":"katabareō","gloss":"to burden","_zh_tw_Gloss":"拖累過","_es_Gloss":"cargar","_zh_Gloss":"拖累过"}],"shortDef":"burdensome, heavy, important; savage, fierce","mediumDef":"burdensome, heavy, important; savage, fierce <br /><b>heavy;</b>, <i>metaphorically</i> <b>burdensome, oppressive</b> or <b>difficult of observance,</b> as precepts, <ref='Mat.23.4'>Mt. 23:4</ref>; <ref='1Jn.5.3'>1Jn. 5:3;</ref> <b>weighty, important, momentous,</b> <ref='Mat.23.23'>Mt. 23:23</ref>; <ref='Act.25.7'>Acts 25:7;</ref> <b>grievous, oppressive, afflictive, violent, savage, fierce</b> <ref='Act.20.29'>Acts 20:29